Costume-> Color

Color...  is the first selection under the Costume pull-down menu.
When this tool is invoked with an object selected, it can be used to
set the color of the object. When invoked without any object selected,
it does not affect any object in the main scene. The default color
editor is an RGB color editor, which lets you set the Red, Green and
Blue color values for the object selected. Other types of color
sliders (HSV, RGB, Value etc.) can be chosen by selecting the
appropriate option under the "Sliders" drop down menu.

HSV sliders are used to set the Hue, Saturation and Value of color of
an object. The Value slider is used to control the intensity of the
color of the selected object.

To use the color wheel, simply move the small circle in the color
wheel to the desired color. As you do so, you will see the color of
your object change to reflect the changes you are making in the
editor.
 
